  "body": "Currently, invalid states for transactions are computed by checking if the `value` field is null. When a invalid input checked within a saga for a field, it sets the `value` field to null. This does not allow for custom / inline error messages as the cause of the error is not known from the UI side ( as it can only tell if the field is valid or invalid, but not why ). Instead, for each field we can introduce a `error` field that is of type `string | null`. This would allow validators within sagas to put error messages for components to display to the user.\r\n\r\nExample field:\r\nPreviously: \r\n```ts \r\nAppState['transactions']['fields']['gasLimit'] === { raw: string, value: Wei | null }\r\n```\r\nAfter: \r\n```ts\r\nAppState['transactions']['fields']['gasLimit'] === { raw: string, value: Wei | null, error: string | null }\r\n```",
