    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I know I originally did an `error` field, but I think it'd actually be more flexible to do a `message` field. There've been a lot of discussions that involve showing positive things (ENS resolution, you've sent to this address before etc.) and warnings (You've never sent to this address before, abnormally high gas, sending ETH to contract.) So it would be nice to have an `InputMessage` type that takes in a string / react element for display, and a type `danger|warning|success|info` for how to display.\r\n\r\nLet me know if that sounds good, or more trouble than it's worth.",
